    "summary": "DatoCMS exposes a GraphQL Content Delivery API, an HTTP Content Management API, a remote MCP server at `https://mcp.datocms.com`, and the `datocms` npm CLI; all require authentication via DatoCMS-issued API tokens or OAuth depending on the surface.",
    "description": "DatoCMS is a headless content management system for modeling, managing, and delivering structured content to websites and applications. It provides APIs and tooling for content delivery, content management, schema migrations, and AI-assisted workflows.",
    "credentials": {
      "api_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "DatoCMS API token",
        "generateUrl": "https://www.datocms.com/docs/content-management-api/authentication",
        "setup": "In your DatoCMS project admin area (`http://your-project.admin.datocms.com`), open **Project Settings → API Tokens**. Every project has a default read-only token, and you can create custom tokens with role-based permissions there. For Content Delivery API access, ensure the token has the **Access the Content Delivery API** or **Access the Content Delivery API in Preview Mode** flag enabled as described in [Content Delivery API authentication](https://www.datocms.com/docs/content-delivery-api/authentication). For CLI usage, the token must have `can_access_cma: true` as described in [Authenticate with an API token](https://www.datocms.com/docs/cli/authenticate-with-api-token)."
      },
      "cli_oauth": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "DatoCMS CLI OAuth login",
        "generateUrl": "https://www.datocms.com/docs/cli",
        "setup": "Install the CLI, then run `npx datocms login`. Your browser opens for DatoCMS account authorization, and the CLI stores credentials locally in `~/.config/datocms/credentials.json` as described in [CLI Overview](https://www.datocms.com/docs/cli)."
      }
    },
